{"id":60216,"title":"Haemophagocytic lymphohistiocytosis (HLH): case series in tertiary referral hospital over three years.","abstract":"Haemophagocytic lymphohistiocytosis (HLH) is a rare but potentially fatal disease of normal but overactive histiocytes and lymphocytes that commonly appears in infancy, although it has been seen in all age groups. We are reporting a series of 5 cases of HLH in young adult and paediatric patients identified over three years.","date":"2014-06-30","categories":"Hemic and Lymphatic Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24974508","annotations":[{"name":"Disease","weight":0.508055,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disease"},{"name":"Pediatrics","weight":0.375104,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pediatrics"},{"name":"Infant","weight":0.360168,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infant"},{"name":"Hospital","weight":0.359972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hospital"},{"name":"Adult","weight":0.224864,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adult"},{"name":"Lymphocyte","weight":0.059743,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lymphocyte"},{"name":"Tertiary referral hospital","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tertiary_referral_hospital"},{"name":"Hemophagocytic lymphohistiocytosis","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hemophagocytic_lymphohistiocytosis"},{"name":"Histiocyte","weight":0.0290048,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Histiocyte"},{"name":"Normal distribution","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Normal_distribution"},{"name":"Basic-helix-loop-helix","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Basic-helix-loop-helix"},{"name":"Referral (medicine)","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Referral_(medicine)"},{"name":"Case series","weight":0.0158689,"wikip